Calm down, my dear...
<i>Every bit of me afflicted with this eldritch malaise,</i>

297
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,380
God...
<i>My life is now ruined</i>

298
00:25:31,380 --> 00:25:34,600
<i>My life is now ruined</i>

299
00:25:34,600 --> 00:25:36,660
Calm down...
<i>My life is now ruined</i>

300
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:37,450
<i>O Lord</i>

301
00:25:37,450 --> 00:25:39,124
Mum --
<i>O Lord</i>

302
00:25:39,124 --> 00:25:41,514
<i>O Lord</i>

303
00:25:41,514 --> 00:25:42,030
<i>Decide my fate</i>

304
00:25:42,030 --> 00:25:43,781
Jan'e Alam?
<i>Decide my fate</i>

305
00:25:43,781 --> 00:25:47,690
<i>Decide my fate</i>

306
00:25:47,690 --> 00:25:48,140
Jan'e Alam?

307
00:25:48,140 --> 00:25:50,060
Jan'e Alam?
<i>Hear my prayer</i>

308
00:25:50,060 --> 00:25:51,210
Wake up!
<i>Hear my prayer</i>

309
00:25:51,210 --> 00:25:54,430
What happened to you?
<i>Hear my prayer</i>

310
00:25:54,430 --> 00:25:58,200
You don't get it, Ma'am. The Chairman's having a meeting inside.

311
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,420
So?

312
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:01,044
You can't go inside.

313
00:26:01,044 --> 00:26:02,423
You don't know

314
00:26:02,423 --> 00:26:04,154
What Mr Shan's like.

315
00:26:04,154 --> 00:26:06,976
He'd leave every other thing to hear the poor out.

316
00:26:06,976 --> 00:26:10,736
The Headmistress has asked me not to allow anyone in during meetings.

317
00:26:10,736 --> 00:26:14,290
Look, sir, it's very important that I meet Mr Shan.

318
00:26:14,290 --> 00:26:15,693
I've got to talk to him.

319
00:26:15,693 --> 00:26:17,057
Let's see who can stop me!

320
00:26:17,057 --> 00:26:18,180
Step aside.
-Hey!

321
00:26:18,180 --> 00:26:21,070
Wait, Ma'am!
-Let go!

322
00:26:21,070 --> 00:26:22,141
Hey!

323
00:26:22,141 --> 00:26:24,760
How'd you get in -- Why did you let her in?

324
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:28,654
I tried to stop her, Ma'am, but she barged in.

325
00:26:28,654 --> 00:26:31,750
She said she's got to talk to the Chairman about something.

326
00:26:31,750 --> 00:26:33,258
Just a minute.

327
00:26:33,478 --> 00:26:34,840
So you want to talk to me?

328
00:26:34,840 --> 00:26:38,460
Yes, Mr Shan. I want to talk to you.

329
00:26:38,460 --> 00:26:39,344
Pray tell?

330
00:26:39,344 --> 00:26:41,990
Mr Shan, I want to tell you something

331
00:26:41,990 --> 00:26:44,164
About what's going on in your school.

332
00:26:44,164 --> 00:26:46,425
They're just looking after their own!

333
00:26:46,425 --> 00:26:47,975
You'd said, hadn't you,

334
00:26:47,975 --> 00:26:50,260
That there's no difference between the rich and the poor?

335
00:26:50,260 --> 00:26:52,104
But why differentiate between the kids?

336
00:26:52,104 --> 00:26:53,146
What do you mean?

337
00:26:53,146 --> 00:26:54,196
I don't get it.

338
00:26:54,196 --> 00:26:55,930
Sir -- It's -- The teacher, you know --

339
00:26:55,930 --> 00:26:58,543
She gave her niece the first place,

340
00:26:58,543 --> 00:27:02,858
And my daughter the second place.

341
00:27:02,858 --> 00:27:04,564
What's she saying, Madame Headmistress?

342
00:27:04,564 --> 00:27:05,919
Who's she talking about?

343
00:27:05,919 --> 00:27:07,064
Sir --

344
00:27:07,064 --> 00:27:08,645
I have no idea.

345
00:27:08,645 --> 00:27:12,765
I don't know what she's talking about -- I don't get it.

346
00:27:12,765 --> 00:27:14,860
No need to cover it up, Ma'am.

347
00:27:14,860 --> 00:27:16,221
You know everything.

348
00:27:16,221 --> 00:27:18,720
I know the teacher, Mr Shan!

349
00:27:18,720 --> 00:27:20,484
Her name's Meryem!

350
00:27:20,484 --> 00:27:24,590
Her niece and my daughter are in the same class.

351
00:27:24,590 --> 00:27:26,195
They're class-fellows.

352
00:27:26,195 --> 00:27:29,395
They've scored the same marks.

353
00:27:29,395 --> 00:27:31,523
But she awarded

354
00:27:31,523 --> 00:27:33,617
The first place to her niece...

355
00:27:33,617 --> 00:27:36,695
And the second place to my daughter.

356
00:27:36,695 --> 00:27:38,895
These folks think

357
00:27:38,895 --> 00:27:40,490
That we're poor...

358
00:27:40,490 --> 00:27:41,806
What would we know about

359
00:27:41,806 --> 00:27:43,278
The first place

360
00:27:43,278 --> 00:27:45,902
And second place?

361
00:27:46,480 --> 00:27:47,831
But sir,

362
00:27:47,831 --> 00:27:52,020
I expect fairness from you. My daughter's been crying so much...

363
00:27:52,020 --> 00:27:54,500
She's always stood first!

364
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,433
Please don't cry.

365
00:27:56,433 --> 00:27:57,981
Please.

366
00:27:59,060 --> 00:28:01,549
I say, take her to the waiting area.

367
00:28:01,549 --> 00:28:03,329
Please wait. I'll call you.

368
00:28:03,329 --> 00:28:05,129
Thank you, Mr Shan,

369
00:28:05,129 --> 00:28:07,293
Thank you so much.

370
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:14,737
Mr Alam,

371
00:28:14,737 --> 00:28:17,030
You're alright.

372
00:28:17,030 --> 00:28:19,230
Just continue taking your medicines.

373
00:28:19,230 --> 00:28:22,894
You'd get worse if you stopped taking them.

374
00:28:25,541 --> 00:28:26,760
Thank you, Doctor.

375
00:28:26,760 --> 00:28:28,049
Take care.

376
00:28:28,049 --> 00:28:30,859
Alright. Nasrin, leave the doctor outside.

377
00:28:38,190 --> 00:28:41,290
Why didn't you take your medicines?

378
00:28:41,290 --> 00:28:46,780
You do know that your depression will get worse if you don't take your medicines, don't you?

379
00:28:46,780 --> 00:28:52,870
No medicine in this world can possibly help

380
00:28:52,870 --> 00:28:57,886
Someone who's been cursed by the sobs of the helpless.

381
00:29:06,120 --> 00:29:11,200
But yes, a lethal injection

382
00:29:11,200 --> 00:29:13,850
Could surely ease the woes of life...

383
00:29:13,850 --> 00:29:15,584
Does ease the woes of life...
-Shut up.

384
00:29:16,146 --> 00:29:18,896
Don't say that again.

385
00:29:22,390 --> 00:29:25,036
You're a wise man.

386
00:29:25,240 --> 00:29:27,508
Just look at what you're saying.

387
00:29:27,508 --> 00:29:30,163
What would happen to me?

388
00:29:30,410 --> 00:29:32,598
Do you know that despair is sinful, too?

389
00:29:32,598 --> 00:29:36,085
It displeases the Lord.

390
00:29:37,660 --> 00:29:42,227
Doesn't everything that Jan'e Alam does?

391
00:29:42,227 --> 00:29:43,728
What is going on?

392
00:29:43,728 --> 00:29:48,085
Despite your --
-I have no idea what she was talking about.

393
00:29:48,085 --> 00:29:51,500
I don't know anything.
-How come you don't know?

394
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:52,916
S --
I say...

395
00:29:52,916 --> 00:29:54,455
What's her name?

396
00:29:54,455 --> 00:29:55,436
Meryem.

397
00:29:55,436 --> 00:29:56,709
Please call her here.

398
00:29:56,709 --> 00:30:00,010
But sir --
-I'm saying call her here.

399
00:30:00,010 --> 00:30:03,116
Right now. I want to talk to her. Please.

400
00:30:03,116 --> 00:30:04,693
Okay.

401
00:30:10,840 --> 00:30:11,550
Hello?

402
00:30:11,550 --> 00:30:12,857
No.

403
00:30:12,996 --> 00:30:15,864
Send Miss Meryem to my office.

404
00:30:15,864 --> 00:30:17,598
Quickly.

405
00:30:23,450 --> 00:30:25,035
Look, Madame Headmistress,

406
00:30:25,035 --> 00:30:29,772
I can't tolerate any kind of injustice in my school.

407
00:30:33,180 --> 00:30:35,920
Alright, listen to this.

408
00:30:35,920 --> 00:30:37,980
Listen carefully.

409
00:30:37,980 --> 00:30:40,646
Don't jump to a 'no', okay?

410
00:30:44,500 --> 00:30:45,980
My dear,

411
00:30:45,980 --> 00:30:48,063
I say you

412
00:30:48,063 --> 00:30:51,377
Think seriously about your marriage.

413
00:30:52,018 --> 00:30:54,380
I'm confident

414
00:30:54,380 --> 00:30:58,318
That you'll be better quickly.

415
00:31:00,690 --> 00:31:03,988
I've married once already...

416
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:07,462
Just forget all of that...

417
00:31:08,009 --> 00:31:15,600
How can someone forget the destruction of another,

418
00:31:15,600 --> 00:31:21,520
Especially when one's responsible for it?

419
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:23,426
Jan'e Alam...

420
00:31:23,426 --> 00:31:26,344
If you keep on thinking like this -

421
00:31:26,344 --> 00:31:29,340
Heavens forbid - Your condition will only get worse.

422
00:31:29,340 --> 00:31:31,516
Please, don't...

423
00:31:34,360 --> 00:31:37,240
I feel the same way.

424
00:31:39,070 --> 00:31:41,894
I won't get better.

425
00:31:43,190 --> 00:31:44,800
No.

426
00:31:44,800 --> 00:31:47,350
Don't ever say that.

427
00:31:47,350 --> 00:31:48,598
Okay?

428
00:31:48,598 --> 00:31:50,354
Never.

429
00:31:59,380 --> 00:32:02,563
Look, Aunt, I've scored 100 marks!
-Really?

430
00:32:02,563 --> 00:32:05,152
I made the report cards but didn't notice!

431
00:32:05,152 --> 00:32:06,723
What?

432
00:32:07,720 --> 00:32:10,566
Why didn't you tell me?

433
00:32:10,566 --> 00:32:12,830
Do you know how tensed I was, Aunt?

434
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:17,230
Could I have seen this broad smile if I'd told you before?

435
00:32:17,680 --> 00:32:19,230
Congratulations, Humna!

436
00:32:19,230 --> 00:32:20,360
Thank you, Aunt!

437
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:23,480
Alright, come and sit here. Tell me what you want as a gift.

438
00:32:23,480 --> 00:32:24,570
Gift?

439
00:32:24,570 --> 00:32:26,610
How much money have you got again?

440
00:32:26,610 --> 00:32:27,340
Let's say...

441
00:32:27,340 --> 00:32:28,830
Let's say... Five bags?

442
00:32:28,830 --> 00:32:30,587
5,000?

443
00:32:30,791 --> 00:32:32,730
I'll have to think, then!

444
00:32:32,730 --> 00:32:33,569
Oh?

445
00:32:33,569 --> 00:32:37,250
Then, think hard about what you'd want!
-Miss...

446
00:32:37,250 --> 00:32:39,430
The Headmistress has called you to her office.

447
00:32:39,430 --> 00:32:40,939
I'm coming.

448
00:32:42,020 --> 00:32:43,990
I'll be back, okay?

449
00:33:03,135 --> 00:33:06,490
How long will this go on?

450
00:33:06,490 --> 00:33:10,866
How long will you continue to torment yourself?

451
00:33:18,270 --> 00:33:23,121
Have you seen the scar on Erum's forehead, Mum?

452
00:33:25,470 --> 00:33:30,500
I feel that my past

453
00:33:30,500 --> 00:33:34,306
Is etched in those scars.

454
00:33:35,952 --> 00:33:39,326
Whenever I look at her forehead,

455
00:33:39,326 --> 00:33:43,873
I feel like my past is standing before me,

456
00:33:43,873 --> 00:33:47,335
Screaming,

457
00:33:47,335 --> 00:33:53,380
For every single bit of injustice done to me,

458
00:33:53,380 --> 00:33:55,500
My Lord God

459
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:58,776
Will make you pay!

460
00:33:58,980 --> 00:34:02,650
'Jan'e Alam',

461
00:34:02,650 --> 00:34:06,412
'Watch how the Lord chastens you!'

462
00:34:11,930 --> 00:34:13,743
God...

463
00:34:19,070 --> 00:34:23,200
<i>I</i> should've been punished for my sins.

464
00:34:23,829 --> 00:34:26,966
Set me free from this life.

465
00:34:26,966 --> 00:34:31,230
I'm in great pain.

466
00:34:32,890 --> 00:34:38,130
Meryem's curse should've destroyed Jan'e Alam and spared my sister...

467
00:34:40,740 --> 00:34:44,230
My sister's suffered a lot...

468
00:34:51,990 --> 00:34:54,862
Erum's so innocent, isn't she?

469
00:34:56,590 --> 00:35:00,371
She still thinks I'm an angel...

470
00:35:00,810 --> 00:35:05,140
If only she found out

471
00:35:05,140 --> 00:35:09,033
That she's been punished for <i>my</i> sins...

472
00:35:10,110 --> 00:35:13,636
How much she'd grow to despise me...

473
00:35:16,538 --> 00:35:17,743
Look, Miss,

474
00:35:17,743 --> 00:35:19,413
This is a disciplined school,

475
00:35:19,413 --> 00:35:22,208
And I will not tolerate

476
00:35:22,208 --> 00:35:25,370
Any kind of injustice to any student.

477
00:35:25,370 --> 00:35:29,960
If your niece studies here, don't ever think that you can favour her.

478
00:35:29,960 --> 00:35:31,680
It's nothing like that, sir!

479
00:35:31,680 --> 00:35:34,975
I've worked on the results with utmost fairness.
-Fairness, you say?

480
00:35:34,975 --> 00:35:38,340
When your niece and my daughter scored the same marks,

481
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:41,490
Why did you award the first place to your niece?

482
00:35:41,490 --> 00:35:45,880
Your daughter's stood second because --
-Oh? Can't kids fall sick?

483
00:35:45,880 --> 00:35:49,850
She pushed my daughter back just because she had a fever for one day?

484
00:35:49,850 --> 00:35:52,717
What kind of fairness is that?

485
00:35:52,717 --> 00:35:55,531
It's noth --
-Please...

486
00:35:55,970 --> 00:35:59,710
I don't want any dispute here.

487
00:35:59,901 --> 00:36:01,025
Please,

488
00:36:01,025 --> 00:36:02,617
Revise the results.

489
00:36:02,617 --> 00:36:06,440
I'll announce the new results in the class tomorrow in person.

490
00:36:06,440 --> 00:36:10,581
But, sir --
-I don't like having to repeat myself.

491
00:36:10,581 --> 00:36:15,965
You will revise the results and award both the girls the first place.

492
00:36:16,420 --> 00:36:17,954
It's your responsibility now.

493
00:36:17,954 --> 00:36:19,220
Are we clear?

494
00:36:19,220 --> 00:36:21,078
Okay, sir.
-Yes, sir.

495
00:36:26,090 --> 00:36:30,095
Bleedin' nepotist!

